{"id": "552b9b5a-d3de-4d39-afe1-fe734d4c4262", "task_id": "d0145737-4c7e-4fd1-b149-812c1aba9262", "path": "templates/index.html", "artifact_type": "file", "content": "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n    <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n    <title>CYBER_OS // ACCESS_GATEWAY</title>\n    <link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"{{ url_for('static', path='/style.css') }}\">\n</head>\n<body>\n    <div class=\"container\">\n        <div class=\"login-card\">\n            <!-- Cyberpunk Header with Glitch Effect -->\n            <h1 class=\"title glitch\" data-text=\"NEURAL_LINK\">NEURAL_LINK</h1>\n            \n            <form action=\"/login\" method=\"post\" autocomplete=\"off\">\n                <div class=\"form-group\">\n                    <label for=\"username\">User Identity</label>\n                    <input \n                        type=\"text\" \n                        id=\"username\" \n                        name=\"username\" \n                        value=\"{{ username if username else '' }}\" \n                        required \n                        placeholder=\"[ID_ALPHA_8]\"\n                        autofocus\n                    >\n                </div>\n                \n                <div class=\"form-group\">\n                    <label for=\"access_code\">Access Code</label>\n                    <input \n                        type=\"password\" \n                        id=\"access_code\" \n                        name=\"access_code\" \n                        required \n                        placeholder=\"********\"\n                    >\n                </div>\n\n                <button type=\"submit\" class=\"login-btn\">\n                    ESTABLISH UPLINK\n                </button>\n            </form>\n\n            <!-- Dynamic Feedback Area -->\n            {% if error %}\n            <div class=\"error-msg\">\n                >> SYSTEM_ALERT: {{ error }}\n            </div>\n            {% endif %}\n\n            {% if success %}\n            <div class=\"success-msg\">\n                >> SUCCESS: {{ message }}\n            </div>\n            {% endif %}\n\n            <!-- Footer Terminal Deco -->\n            <div style=\"margin-top: 25px; font-size: 0.6rem; opacity: 0.5; color: var(--neon-cyan);\">\n                <p id=\"terminal-status\">STATION_ID: NODE_04 // PORT: 8000</p>\n                <p id=\"typewriter\"></p>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <script>\n        /**\n         * Cyberpunk UI Enhancements\n         */\n        const statusText = \"BOOTING_ENCRYPTION_MODULES... READY.\";\n        let charIndex = 0;\n        const speed = 40;\n\n        function typeEffect() {\n            const target = document.getElementById(\"typewriter\");\n            if (charIndex < statusText.length) {\n                target.textContent += statusText.charAt(charIndex);\n                charIndex++;\n                setTimeout(typeEffect, speed);\n            }\n        }\n\n        // Subtle input interaction sound or effect would go here\n        document.querySelectorAll('input').forEach(input => {\n            input.addEventListener('focus', () => {\n                console.log(\"Node focused: \" + input.id);\n            });\n        });\n\n        window.onload = typeEffect;\n    </script>\n</body>\n</html>", "patches": [], "metadata": {"language": "html", "framework": "static_html", "explanation": "This HTML template uses Jinja2 syntax to integrate with the FastAPI backend. It features a high-fidelity cyberpunk layout including a glitch-effect title, neon-styled form inputs, and conditional rendering for error/success messages. It also includes a Vanilla JS typewriter effect to enhance the terminal atmosphere and links correctly to the static CSS file via FastAPI's url_for utility.", "dependencies": []}, "created_at": "2026-05-17 13:57:43.848447"}